NOTICE — Responsible Use

This tool is intended for defensive security research only. It is designed to:

  - Detect supply chain backdoors in open-source dependencies
  - Audit your own codebases for accidental security anti-patterns
  - Support red-team / blue-team exercises with authorization
  - Advance academic research in software supply chain security

It is NOT intended for:

  - Evading detection of malicious code you are authoring
  - Scanning systems or codebases without explicit authorization
  - Any activity that violates applicable laws or terms of service

Supply chain attacks like XZ Utils (CVE-2024-3094), event-stream (npm),
and color/npm highlighted the critical need for automated backdoor detection
in open-source dependencies. This tool exists to help defenders stay ahead.

By using this software, you agree to use it responsibly and in compliance
with all applicable laws. The authors accept no liability for misuse.
